documents.Summary:
{
    "covered": "- Your Home if You have ‘Building’ insurance;
- General Contents while in Your Home if You have ‘Contents’ insurance;
- Loss or damage caused by Listed Events which include:
  - Accidental breakage of glass
  - Animal damage
  - Deliberate or intentional act
  - Earthquake
  - Escape of water or liquid
  - Explosion
  - Fire
  - Flood or Rainwater Run-off
  - Impact
  - Lightning
  - Riot or civil commotion
  - Storm
  - Storm Surge or tsunami
  - Theft or attempted theft
- Optional benefits include:
  - Accidental damage
  - Electrical motor burnout
  - Cover for liability
  - Additional benefits (e.g., Contents in transit, Food spoilage, Identity theft, Landscaping, etc.)",
    "not-covered": "- Any loss or damage caused by intentionally breaking the item;
- Loss or damage by deliberate or intentional acts by You, Your Family, or anyone permitted at the Site;
- Loss or damage due to illegal activities;
- Loss or damage during the unoccupied period exceeding 60 consecutive days;
- General Exclusions apply including:
  - Actions of the Sea;
  - Erosion, deterioration, or earth movement;
  - Cyber incidents (e.g., computer breakdown);
  - Communicable diseases;",
    "additional-info": "- Your responsibilities include maintaining your Home and notifying Us if the Home is unoccupied or if significant changes occur;
- Coverage is offered under various levels including 'Plus' and 'Standard', with different coverage levels for 'Building' and 'Contents';
- The policy may automatically renew with the inclusion of inflation adjustments unless otherwise specified.",
    "gotchas": "- Claims may be denied if obligations, such as maintaining up-to-date contact details or timely payment of premiums, are not met;
- If You make a claim that is denied, You may be required to cover costs or contribute to recovery actions, especially if You have to pursue legal actions on your own;
- Excess amounts may apply differently based on the nature of the claim (Building vs. Contents); If both claims are made, only one Excess of the higher amount applies.
- Important timeline checks for claims must be met (e.g., notifying within specified periods);"
}
